We'd like you to meet <b>Carlo</b>, our featured citizen of the week!<br><br>Carlo has been a citizen of Millsberry ever since December 9th, 2006. He's been kicking it at his <a href='/home/?user=carlo_619'>53396 Bunker Park</a> home where he holds down the fort. Carlo's favorite colors are red, dark blue, and gold. Luckily with his disco dance floor, he can enjoy all of them at the same time. <br><br>Carlo has been known to be a music enthusiast. The disco dance floor also comes in handy when he's breaking it down to his favorite techno tunes. If you're not captivated by the bright lights, you can always feast your eyes on Carlo's movie projection screen. The characters always seem larger than life, but don't worry; it's just movie magic.<br><br>When you're done practicing the free art of rhythmic expression (a.k.a. dancing), you can make your way to Carlo's spacious yet well-accommodated living room. Feel free to kick back on the comfy Sylvie sofa or have a friendly match on Carlo's vintage dome hockey game. Time flies when you're having fun. Fortunately, there's a yellow monster clock on the wall to monitor just how much fun you're having. <br><br>On a nice day, fresh air is a must-have. You can head out to Carlo's backyard, where adventure is waiting. If speed is your thing, you'll find several different options that are sure to get your heart pumping. There's a kayak for your laid-back side. If you want to pick things up a bit, there's also a bicycle. As for the bobsled and the ATV, we recommend that you enjoy those on the proper terrain. <br><br>Next time you see Carlo, give him a high five, and congratulate him on being such an outstanding citizen.<br></div>
